> I also agree that we have resolved the discrepancy between our UHF 
> wave functions, and we're working now to obtain the CCSD NOs using the 
> Cs symmetry-broken orbitals as a reference.  These NOs are obtained by 
> diagonalization of the spin-orbital density (including its UHF 
> component), and the occupations AJ has reported are the sum of the 
> alpha and beta contributions.  I think this is consistent with your 
> approach.
