    <br>
    On 8/4/2015 10:52 AM, T. Daniel Crawford wrote:
    <blockquote type="cite">
      <div dir="ltr">Dear Hans,
        <div><br>
        </div>
        <div>I also agree that we have resolved the discrepancy between
          our UHF wave functions, and we're working now to obtain the
          CCSD NOs using the Cs symmetry-broken orbitals as a
          reference.  These NOs are obtained by diagonalization of the
          spin-orbital density (including its UHF component), and the
          occupations AJ has reported are the sum of the alpha and beta
          contributions.  I think this is consistent with your approach.</div>
        <div><br>
        </div>
        <div>Our stability code has gone through an overhaul in the last
          two weeks, which has slowed our efforts further, but obtaining
          the data for this paper is high on our priority list.  We'll
          let you know as soon as we have useful results.</div>
        <div><br>
        </div>
        <div>Best regards,</div>
        <div><br>
        </div>
        <div>-Daniel</div>
